Catcher Technology, EVA Airways, Hon Hai: Taiwan Stocks Preview

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-06-20T00:36:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/catcher-technology-eva-airways-hon-hai-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Taiex Index fell 18.33, or 0.2 percent, to 8,636.10.  Catcher Technology Co. (2474 TT): The computer casing maker
had its share-price estimate raised to NT$216 from NT$190 at UBS
AG. The brokerage maintained a “buy” rating on the company.
The stock dropped 2.6 percent to NT$167.50.  EVA Airways Corp. (2618)  (2618 TT): Taiwan’s second-largest
carrier plans to spend NT$100 billion ($3.5 billion) buying 25
aircrafts as early as the second half, the Economic Daily News
reported today, citing President Chang Kuo-Wei. The airline
plans to buy 10 777-300 ER planes from Boeing Co. and 15 A321
from Airbus SAS, the report cited Chang as saying. The stock
retreated 1.1 percent to NT$26.50.  Hon Hai Precision Industry Co. (2317 TT): Foxconn
Technology Group will assemble the camera modules for Apple
Inc.’s iPad 3, the Commercial Times reported, without saying
where it got the information. The camera module will be equipped
with an 8-megapixel image censor, compared with the 5-megapixel
censors used in iPad 2, according to the report. The stock
advanced 0.3 percent to NT$98.70.  To contact the reporter on this story:
